            "id": "4551713",
            "title": "European indexes dip ahead of key U.S. inflation data",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\">London (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/UKX\" title=\"FTSE 100 Index\">UKX</a></span>) +0.11% to 10,414.</p>\n<p>Germany (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/DAX:IND\" title=\"DAX Germany Index\">DAX:IND</a>) -0.09% to 24,831.<span> </span></p>\n<p>France (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CAC:IND\" title=\"CAC 40 France Index\">CAC:IND</a>) -0.42% to 8,306. </p>\n<p>In other parts of Europe,<span> consumer prices in Switzerland rose by 0.1% Y/Y in January.</span></p>\n<p><a data-discover=\"true\" href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4551712-spain-inflation-drops-to-23-in-january#source=url_first_level%3Amarket-news%7Csection%3Amarket-pulse%7Csection_asset%3Anews_title\">Spain inflation drops to 2.3% in January</a>.</p>\n<p>The pan-European <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/STOXX\">Stoxx 600</a> (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/STOXX\" title=\"STOXX Europe 600 Index\">STOXX</a>) moved 0.11% lower to 617.9, after the latest sell-off on Wall Street over AI fears, with <span>most sectors and major bourses in negative territory. I</span>nvestors kep a cautious stance ahead of key U.S. inflation numbers that could impact the Federal Reserve’s next policy moves. Tech names faced renewed selling pressure amid growing concerns over the long-term sustainability<span> of AI spending.</span></p>\n<p><strong>Coming up in the session:</strong> Euro Area trade balance expected shortly<strong>.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>In the bond market</strong>, the U.S. 10-year Treasury yield was up 2 basis points to 4.12%. </p>\n<p>Germany's 10-year yield was up less than 1 basis point to 2.78%.</p>\n<p>The UK's 10-year yield was up less than 1 basis point to 4.46%.</p>\n<p><strong>Currencies:</strong> (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/EUR:USD\" title=\"Euro / US Dollar\">EUR:USD</a>) (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GBP:USD\" title=\"British Pound / US Dollar\">GBP:USD</a>) (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CHF:USD\" title=\"Swiss Franc / US Dollar\">CHF:USD</a>)</p>\n<p><strong>ETFs:</strong> (NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/EWG\">EWG</a>), (NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GF\">GF</a>), (NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/EWI\">EWI</a>), (NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/EWQ\">EWQ</a>), (NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/FGM\">FGM</a>), (NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/DAX\">DAX</a>), (NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/FLGR\">FLGR</a>), (NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/FXB\">FXB</a>), (NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/EWU\">EWU</a>), (NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/FKU\">FKU</a>), (BATS:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/EWUS\">EWUS</a>), (NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/FLGB\">FLGB</a>), (NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GREK\">GREK</a>)</p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
